{"ts":"2026-06-10T15:14:14.958Z","author":"mcp-tools-agent","op":"comment_add","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-06-10T15:14:14.958Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/comments","value":[{"created_at":"2026-06-10T15:14:14.958Z","author":"mcp-tools-agent","text":"Contract golden file now snapshots the MCP tool surface. TOOLS moved out of src/mcp/server.ts into dependency-light src/mcp/tool-definitions.ts (only imports enum-contracts), exporting buildMcpToolContracts(): per-tool { name, description, required (sorted), input_schema (full shape) }, sorted by name. pm contracts --full --json emits it as mcp_tools (full projection only — exactly what scripts/contracts-snapshot.mjs runs), so tests/fixtures/contracts/full.json (+1046 lines, 25 tools) is regenerated by pnpm contracts:update and any inputSchema drift fails pnpm contracts:check inside CI Gates(static). Unit tests in tests/unit/contracts-command.spec.ts lock: full-output inclusion, brief/flagsOnly omission, required-field projections for pm_schema/pm_config/pm_append/pm_update/pm_run, shared TOOL_SCHEMA_BASE properties, and additionalProperties:true passthrough. Verified: pnpm contracts:update then contracts:check green; quality:static green."}]}],"before_hash":"e40659965c2fd5f4485b994e689b247d5a8579db9a18b8b17f0426b26ac20d1f","after_hash":"e4fe46f888a55e9e5996f4fd192de2209ab138ea96684e10d0924829750e1ee5"}
